sparate parts of society. These distinctive features allow them, more than any other institution, to innovate in response to new problems and opportunities. Presenting numerous case studies that show how research universities play these three roles and why they matter, this book offers a fresh and stirring defense of the research university.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 15. Sep 2020) 0aAcademic-industrial collaborationzUnited States. 0aFederal aid to researchzUnited States. 0aResearch institutesxSocial aspectszUnited States. 0aResearch instituteszUnited StatesxSocial aspects. 0aUniversities and collegeszUnited States. 4aUniversities. 4adiscovery. 4afederal grants. 4ahigh-technology industries. 4ainnovation. 4anetworks. 4aorganizational theory. 4aresearch and development. 4ascience. 4asociology. 7aEDUCATION / Higher.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUP Complete eBook-Package 2018z978311070368940uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978150360709540uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781503607095423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781503607095.jpg  a978-3-11-070368-9  SUP Complete eBook-Package 2018b2018  aGBV-deGruyter-alles